    <summary>
      <para>The <newTerm>inline image</newTerm> allows embedding an image inline.</para>
    </summary>
    <introduction>
      <autoOutline lead="none" excludeRelatedTopics="true" />
    </introduction>
    <section address="Syntax">
      <title>Syntax</title>
      <content>
        <para>A link preceded by a <codeInline>!</codeInline> (<legacyItalic>bang</legacyItalic>) character.</para>
        <alert>An image occurring by itself in a paragraph will be rendered as a <link xlink:href="6ca84d07-2ee5-42f5-a8e1-29e50e828157">block image</link>.</alert>
        <alert class="tip">Inserting a nonbreaking space after a lone image will cause it to be rendered as an inline image.</alert>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="Example">
      <title>Example</title>
      <content>
        <code title="AMDL" language="none">
This is an inline image:
![](Castle.png "Pirate Sandcastle")

![](Castle.png "Pirate Sandcastle")
is also an inline image.
</code>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="Example Output">
      <title>Example Output</title>
      <content>
        <para>This is an inline image:
<mediaLinkInline><image xlink:href="Castle.png" /></mediaLinkInline></para>
        <para>
          <mediaLinkInline>
            <image xlink:href="Castle.png" />
          </mediaLinkInline>
is also an inline image.</para>
      </content>
    </section>
